        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/metpo/1000059"/>
        <obo:IAO_0000115>A phenotype characterized by a microbe that thrives in low water-activity environments (typically aw &lt; 0.85), where the limiting factor is water activity (aw) rather than solute concentration; distinct from halophily and osmotic tolerance.</obo:IAO_0000115>
